001package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage;
002
003/**
004 * Defines a contract for extracting typed data from a raw object retrieved from storage.
005 *
006 * <p>Implementations of this interface specify how to transform a stored object into a
007 * typed result, allowing the framework to handle various data formats and structures
008 * in a consistent manner.
009 *
010 * <p>The extraction process can optionally involve a sub-key for nested or hierarchical data,
011 * enabling more granular data retrieval when necessary.
012 *
013 * @param <T> The type of the data to be extracted.
014 *
015 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
016 */
017@SuppressWarnings("java:S1452")
018public interface DataExtractor<T> {
019
020   /**
021    * Retrieves the optional sub-key used for nested data extraction.
022    *
023    * <p>If this method returns {@code null}, no sub-key is used in the extraction process.
024    *
025    * @return An {@link Enum} representing the sub-key, or {@code null} if not applicable.
026    */
027   Enum<?> getSubKey();
028
029   /**
030    * Retrieves the primary key identifying the data to be extracted.
031    *
032    * <p>This key corresponds to a logical identifier within the storage system.
033    *
034    * @return An {@link Enum} representing the primary key.
035    */
036   Enum<?> getKey();
037
038   /**
039    * Extracts and transforms the provided raw object into the target type.
040    *
041    * <p>This method applies the extraction logic to convert the stored object into a typed result of type {@code T}.
042    *
043    * @param rawObject The raw object retrieved from storage.
044    * @return The extracted data of type {@code T}.
045    */
046   T extract(Object rawObject);
047
048}
